    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-19T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-19T01:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-19T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 19, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 19—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>253. Legation’s 219, February 11, 6 p.m.<note n="12" xml:id="d489fn12">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from American Consul General Hankow: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“February 18, noon. My February 1[<hi rend="italic">2?</hi>], 4
                                p.m.,<note n="13" xml:id="d489fn13">See telegram No. 184, February
                                3, 11 a.m., from the Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_470">p.
                                    470</ref>.</note> on the subject of the residence of Americans
                            in the interior.</p>
                        <p>Admiral <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WRAYS1">Williams</persName>
                            informs me that the force available at present would prevent efforts to
                            defend more than the Consulate and the Navy godown, including an area of
                            about two blocks.</p>
                        <pb facs="0575" n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/>
                        <p>The British have made complete arrangements for the defense of most of
                            the area of their former concession in the event of an attack by
                            Communists on Hankow or in the event of threatened failure of the
                            Chinese police authority.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
